abstract: California is stepping up its crusade against cybercriminals. On Tuesday, Kamala D. Harris, California’s attorney general, announced the creation of the nation’s largest e-crime unit, a team of 20 investigators and prosecutors whose sole mission will be to thwart and prosecute cybercrimes like identity theft, Internet scams, computer theft, online child pornography and intellectual property theft across the state.

abstract: The medical marijuana industry has become big business in California, but its operators are nervous in the face of stepped-up federal government efforts to shut it down.
snippet: The medical marijuana industry has become big business in California, but its operators are nervous in the face of stepped-up federal government efforts to shut it down.
lead_paragraph: UKIAH, Calif. — An intensifying federal crackdown on growers and sellers of state-authorized medical marijuana has badly shaken the billion-dollar industry, which has sprung up in California since voters approved medical use of the drug in 1996, and has highlighted the stark contradiction between federal and state policies.

abstract: An $8.7 billion settlement with Countrywide Financial in 2008 was supposed to help homeowners like Raul Peña. But that help has not arrived, and he is in the process of selling his house for less than one-third of what he paid.
snippet: An $8.7 billion settlement with Countrywide Financial in 2008 was supposed to help homeowners like Raul Peña. But that help has not arrived, and he is in the process of selling his house for less than one-third of what he paid.
lead_paragraph: Sometime next month, Raul Peña will give up his East Oakland home. Mr. Peña, a 40-year-old dishwasher, used a subprime loan from Countrywide Financial to buy his two-bedroom house for $359,000 in 2005. He is in the process of selling it in a short sale for just $100,000.

abstract: More than 100 people, almost all of them connected to Central California gangs, were arrested this week in the latest effort to curb street gangs, Attorney General Kamala Harris announced.
snippet: More than 100 people, almost all of them connected to Central California gangs, were arrested this week in the latest effort to curb street gangs, Attorney General Kamala Harris announced.
lead_paragraph: More than 100 people, almost all of them connected to Central California gangs, were arrested this week in the latest effort to curb street gangs, Attorney General Kamala Harris announced on Friday. The arrests resulted from an 18-month investigation by the California Department of Justice and other law enforcement agencies that began after a gang network set up operations in Gilroy. The operation also led to the seizure of 44 firearms, 81 stolen vehicles, 3 pounds of methamphetamine and other drugs. A majority of the 103 suspects arrested were gang members with felony convictions, the Department of Justice said. Suspects will face charges relating to auto theft, guns, gangs and the sale of narcotics.

abstract: The decision threatens to derail the Justice Department’s efforts to broker a broad settlement of allegations involving mortgage practices.
snippet: The decision threatens to derail the Justice Department’s efforts to broker a broad settlement of allegations involving mortgage practices.
lead_paragraph: A decision on Friday by a California official to withdraw from negotiations with large banks over their mortgage practices threatens to derail a broad settlement that the Justice Department has been brokering for nearly a year.

abstract: “Restorative justice,” an alternative to punishment for violent criminals, has gained backing in San Francisco, even among some candidates for district attorney.
snippet: “Restorative justice,” an alternative to punishment for violent criminals, has gained backing in San Francisco, even among some candidates for district attorney.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, Betty Renee Ricks stood inside San Francisco County Jail and told 40 inmates how she was first prostituted at age 12, and how one pimp broke her teeth, beat her with hangers until she bled and poured Brut cologne into her wounds.

abstract: The Campaign Against Marijuana Planting, whose costs are shared by the State of California and the federal government, is endangered because of California budget cuts.
snippet: The Campaign Against Marijuana Planting, whose costs are shared by the State of California and the federal government, is endangered because of California budget cuts.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday, a helicopter buzzed over the rugged hills of Mendocino National Forest and lowered five narcotics agents dressed in green fatigues and armed with guns, clippers and machetes. Under the bright blue sky, the crew began to cut down thousands of marijuana plants that were flourishing with the help of an irrigation system in a remote section of the forest in Tehama County.
